-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- Donkey Kong Country.lua — game module for the Archipelago BizHawk connector.
--                          Donkey Kong Country (SNES)
--
-- STATUS: COMMUNITY world. location DETECTION + goal are REAL and SOURCE-DERIVED
-- from the official apworld worlds/dkc (Client.py game_watcher + Locations.py +
-- Levels.py, TheLX5/Archipelago @ branch `dkc`, world_version 1.2.2). The
-- 369-entry location table was GENERATED by JOINING Locations.all_locations
-- (name → AP id) with Levels.location_id_to_level_id (name → [loc_type, level_num,
-- data]) — not hand-copied — so every (AP id → level_num/mask/sanity-index) pair
-- is exact. Mock-verified through MoonSharp against synthetic WRAM/CARTROM. Loads
-- crash-free on any ROM; self-disables on a non-AP cartridge.
--
-- SOURCE: https://github.com/TheLX5/Archipelago  (branch `dkc`, worlds/dkc)
--         game string "Donkey Kong Country", patch_suffix ".apdkc",
--         items_handling 0b111 (FULL remote), base ROM US 1.0
--         MD5 30c5f292ff4cbbfcc00fd8fa96c2de3b.
--
-- MEMORY MODEL (SNI → BizHawk)  — see Research_V2/SNES_BRIDGE_2026-06-12.md
-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
--   The dkc client is an SNIClient. Its SNI addresses translate to BizHawk SNES
--   memory domains:
--     SNI WRAM_START(0xF50000)+off → domain "WRAM",    offset off (= $7E0000+off)
--     SNI ROM_START(0x000000)+off  → domain "CARTROM", offset off (raw ROM file
--                                    offset. Fallbacks "ROM"/"System Bus")
--   DKC1 is a HiROM cartridge, so the internal header at SNES $00:FFC0 lives at
--   ROM **file** offset 0xFFC0 (HiROM places the header there — NOT the LoROM
--   0x7FC0). Both the client read (DKC_ROMHASH_START = 0xFFC0) and the AP patch
--   write (patch.write_bytes(0xFFC0, name)) use file offset 0xFFC0, so this module
--   reads the signature from CARTROM 0xFFC0 directly.
--
--   The client reads these RAM blocks (RAM enum in Client.py); this module reads
--   the same bytes:
--     • stage_flags  = Read(DKC_STAGE_FLAGS = WRAM+0x0583, 0x100)  → WRAM
--         level_flags[level_num] → WRAM 0x0583 + level_num
--     • sanity_flags = Read(DKC_SANITY_FLAGS = WRAM+0x1F800, 0x100) → WRAM
--         sanity_flags[idx]      → WRAM 0x1F800 + idx
--     • nmi_pointer  = Read(WRAM+0x001C, 0x02) → WRAM, u16 LE (0xE6B1 == in map)
--     • current_level= Read(WRAM+0x0563, 0x01) → WRAM
--     • loaded_level = Read(WRAM+0x003E, 0x01) → WRAM (goal: == 0x4C)
--     • brightness   = Read(WRAM+0x051A, 0x01) → WRAM (& 0x0F == 0x0F = full)
--     • kong_letters = Read(WRAM+0x057F, 0x01) → WRAM (& 0x10 == KONG complete)
--   IDENTITY / VALIDATION (mirrors validate_rom): ROM header at CARTROM 0xFFC0
--   begins with "DKC1" and is not all-zero. The AP basepatch bakes this in.
--
-- HOW DKC CHECKS WORK (mirrors Client.py game_watcher; per-location loc_type)
--   Each location carries {loc_type, level_num, data}. game_watcher only processes
--   a location while NOT in a map/transition (nmi_pointer != 0xE6B1) AND at full
--   brightness (brightness & 0x0F == 0x0F):
--     0x00 Level clear : level_flags[level_num] & 0x01
--     0x01 KONG        : level_num == current_level AND kong_flags & 0x10 == 0x10
--     0x02 Bonus       : level_flags[level_num] & data            (data = bonus mask)
--     0x03 Tokens      : level_num == current_level AND sanity_flags[data] & 0x04
--     0x04 Balloons    : level_num == current_level AND sanity_flags[data] & 0x01
--     0x05 Bunches     : level_num == current_level AND sanity_flags[data] & 0x02
--   Reptile Rumble appears under two ids: current_level 0xEA is remapped to 0x01
--   (game_watcher does the same) so its KONG/sanity checks match.
--   The KONG/token/balloon/bunch *sanity* check families are each gated by a
--   per-seed settings byte (kong_checks/token_checks/…). When the server didn't
--   place those locations, they simply aren't in this slot's `locations` filter,
--   so reporting them is impossible anyway — the settings read is therefore not
--   required for correctness and is omitted (it would need a CARTROM settings
--   read that adds no safety here).
--
-- WHAT THIS DOES
--   • poll(): the game_watcher location scan above → AP location ids, gated to the
--     slot's server location set and to the in-game state (game_state set once the
--     player has entered the map, i.e. nmi_pointer has read 0xE6B1 at least once).
--   • is_goal_complete(): loaded_level (WRAM 0x003E) == 0x4C — the K. Rool /
--     Gangplank Galleon credits map the client flags as CLIENT_GOAL.
--   • receive_item(): NO-OP (documented). items_handling = 0b111 (FULL remote) —
--     the dkc client owns ALL item delivery via an intricate, heavily-state-gated
--     set of SRAM/WRAM writes (kong unlock bitmask, ability/animal/object unlock
--     bytes, currency increments, trap counters, an SFX strobe, plus a recv-index
--     handshake at DKC_RECV_INDEX, all gated on full brightness; EnergyLink DK
--     barrels / TrapLink / DeathLink on top). That delivery path is the one piece
--     that needs in-emulator verification before it is wired, so it is left out
--     rather than shipped unverified (a wrong write would corrupt the save or
--     desync the recv-index). Checks + goal above are fully functional regardless.
--
-- MODULE CONTRACT (called by bizhawk_ap_connector.lua)
--   M.init(ctx) / M.poll() -> {ids} / M.is_goal_complete() -> bool /
--   M.receive_item(item_id, meta)
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

local M = {}
M.name = "Donkey Kong Country"

